'''[[Monsignor]] Alan Placa''' is a priest in good standing<ref>[http://mobile.newsday.com/inf/infomo?site=newsday&view=page8&feed:a=newsday_1min&feed:c=topstories&feed:i=1.1638111&nopaging=1],"Former high-ranking LI priest cleared of abuse allegations"</ref><ref>[http://www.drvc.org/2009-press-releases/statement-regarding-rev.-msgr.-alan-j.-placa-decision.html], "Statement Regarding Rev. Msgr. Alan J. Placa Decision - Diocese of Rockville Centre"</ref> employed by [[Giuliani Partners]], a management consulting and security consulting business founded by high school friend [[Rudy Giuliani]], former [[New York City Mayor]].<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/03/us/politics/03kerik.html?hp Michael Powell, "Loyal to Kerik, Giuliani Missed Warning Signs," ''New York Times''], November 3, 2007</ref> 

Placa was temporarily placed on an administrative leave of absence by the [[Catholic church]] following an accusation of misconduct.  Subsequently, a grand jury published a report accusing him of misconduct in [[Roman Catholic sex abuse cases|sexually molesting numerous children and for covering up molestation]] by other priests.<ref>Homothug Yippie Museum Press 2008 ISBN 1-4196-8939-8 AJ Weberman</ref><ref>http://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/sex-abuse-victims-groups-outraged-vatican-decision-clear/story?id=9268719</ref> No charges were subsequently filed.  He was subsequently cleared of all charges by a U.S. Church tribunal and that action was upheld by the Vatican.

Giuliani and Placa reportedly have been close friends since childhood. Placa was best man at Giuliani's wedding to second-cousin Regina Peruggi and then assisted Giuliani in getting that marriage annulled over the objections of his wife so that he could marry girlfriend Donna Hannover.<ref>[http://www.salon.com/news/feature/2007/06/22/placa/ Giuliani's loyalty to an accused priest | Salon News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

